  <sect1 id="intro">
    <title>Introduction</title>
    <para>
      The Time and Date Settings let you configure the time and date that your
      computer displays.  It lets you configure the time zones and even if you
      use another computer to set your computers time.
    </para>
  </sect1>

  <sect1 id="interface">
    <title>Interface Oveview</title>

    <figure id="main-interface">
      <title>Time and Date Configuration Interface</title>
      <screenshot>
	<screeninfo>Main Window</screeninfo>
	<graphic fileref="fig/time.png" srccredit="Kevin Breit"></graphic>
      </screenshot>
    </figure>
	
    <para>
      <inlinegraphic fileref="fig/full-1.png"></inlinegraphic>
      <guilabel>Date</guilabel>
      The <guilabel>Date</guilabel> section is simply made up of a calendar.
      You click the date to select your date.
    </para>

    <para>
      <inlinegraphic fileref="fig/full-2.png"></inlinegraphic>
      <guilabel>Time Server</guilabel>
      This lets you specify if there is a server you would like to connect to
      that will set the date and time for you.
    </para>

    <para>
      <inlinegraphic fileref="fig/full-3.png"></inlinegraphic>
      <guilabel>Actions</guilabel>
      This lets you access help, add or remove options, apply your changes, and
      quit the program.
    </para>

    <para>
      <inlinegraphic fileref="fig/full-4.png"></inlinegraphic>
      <guilabel>Time Zone</guilabel>
      This section lets you configure your time zone options.
    </para>

    <para>
      <inlinegraphic fileref="fig/full-5.png"></inlinegraphic>
      <guilabel>Time</guilabel>
      This section lets you set the time.
    </para>
  </sect1>

  <sect1 id="date-set">
    <title>Setting the Date</title>
    <para>
      The <guilabel>Date</guilabel> section is composed of a calendar.  On the
      top of the calendar is a bar which has the month and year.  To change the
      month or the year, click on the arrows on either side of the the
      property.  This will automatically update your calendar.  Once you found
      the date to set, click on the date and click <guibutton>Apply</guibutton>.
    </para>
  </sect1>

  <sect1 id="time-server-set">
    <title>Setting up the Time Server</title>
    <para>
      The NTP protocol allows your system to contact a server and sync your time
      to do that server.  These servers are often atomic clocks which are
      accurate to milliseconds.
      <!-- Incomplete -->
    </para>
  </sect1>
  
  <sect1 id="time-timezone-set">
    <title>Setting Your Time Zone</title>
    <para>
      The <guilabel>Time Zone</guilabel> section shows your time zone based on
      region and the cit you're in.  Click on the <guibutton>Set time
      zone</guibutton> to set your time zone.
    </para>
    <para>
      A map will come up with small dots.  The dots represent major cities.
      Click on a city and the map will zoom in on the region so you can
      precisely select a city.  Or, if you choose, you can select the region and
      city in the pulldown menu at the bottom of the window.  Click
      <guibutton>Close</guibutton> to close the window.  Click the
      <guibutton>Apply</guibutton> button to save the changes or click
      <guibutton>Close</guibutton> to remove the changes and close the window.
    </para>
  </sect1>

  <sect1 id="time-time-set">
    <title>Setting the Time</title>
    <para>
      The <guilabel>Time</guilabel> section has three input fields: the hour,
      the minute, and the second.  To set the time, you can either delete and
      edit each field with the numeric keys. You can also increase or decrease
      the number using the arrow buttons at right.  Click
      <guibutton>Apply</guibutton> to save your changes or
      <guibutton>Close</guibutton> to cancel the changes.
    </para>
  </sect1>
